Sentencas: In this study, a new inexpensive and simple technique has been developed to produce the anode microtubes used as a cell-support in the tubular SOFC system.
Titulo: A new approach for production of anode microtubes as solid oxide fuel cell support

Sentencas: NiO-GDC (nickel oxide gadolinium doped ceria) rods with different binder contents were fabricated via thermoplastic extrusion.
Titulo: A new approach for production of anode microtubes as solid oxide fuel cell support

Sentencas: The rods were transformed into the tubular shape by wicking out the binder during the controlled debinding processing.
Titulo: A new approach for production of anode microtubes as solid oxide fuel cell support

Sentencas: This was achieved via processing at 600 degrees C and sintering at 1250 degrees C or 1400 degrees C respectively.
Titulo: A new approach for production of anode microtubes as solid oxide fuel cell support

Sentencas: The wall thickness of microtubes was determined by the content of the binder and the ceramic powders.
Titulo: A new approach for production of anode microtubes as solid oxide fuel cell support

Sentencas: The mean wall thickness values of fabricated microtubes were 219 mu m, 272 mu m, and 314 mu m.
Titulo: A new approach for production of anode microtubes as solid oxide fuel cell support

Sentencas: The three-point bending test results show that the best mechanical strength with a bending stress of 164.52 MPa was achieved with the microtubes prepared from the batch 1 containing 20 wt% binder + surfactant and sintered at 1400 degrees C for 5 h.
Titulo: A new approach for production of anode microtubes as solid oxide fuel cell support
